<plot>"Golden Showers" sprays a melancholic mist over the Irish tragedy of CeCe Mavourneen, a lonely, good-hearted Orange County innocent who only tries to make the grade. This darkly original fable of obsession and sunlight was conceived during a sun stroke suffered by writer Ron Johnson and has been brought disturbingly to life by director Dusty DePree. Although comically disquieting, "Golden Showers" takes a serious look at the American Fixation with looking good and the intense commitment to maintain the standard.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?219088</url></doc>
